I haven't yet watched these, but I scrolled through, and it looks to be fairly decent quality. I am a little concerned that I can see a large amount of pixelation here and there. I know it's not a high-res copy, but it's a bit more than what you'd normally get. It also seems to have a little bit more bass than normal, but that could also be partially my headphones. Nothing to be concerned about overall though.

One quick question though. Does anyone know if these are the theatrical or unrated versions? I don't want to be deprived of my gore and plot scenes :D

@arielmercoledi Dude, seriously. Shut up! I scanned this with Avast, Malwarebytes, and whatever my friend uses on her computer, and it came up 100% clean every time. There's nothing in this file that could harm your computer farther than taking up hard drive space.
